The base is wet felted. Each dinosour has long necked, sturdy body, thick legs. one is a solid bright blue and features a simple, stitched smile; the second is a smaller, lying-down figure in a vibrant medium green; and the third is a larger, standing figure in a slightly lighter, chartreuse green

Each figure is handcrafted using a felting technique, resulting in a soft, fuzzy texture, and all share the iconic body shape of the Stegosaurus with four short legs and a short neck. The three dinosaurs exhibit distinct color variations: the left figure is a light seafoam green with a row of pale pink dorsal plates; the center figure is a vibrant medium green with a pattern of black felt spots and a crest of bright magenta plates; and the right figure is a darker forest green/brown with creamy white feet and a row of alternating dark brown and white dorsal plates. All figures feature simple black dot eyes and a cute, stylized aesthetic, clearly intended as charming decorative pieces or craft supplies.

The collection features two distinct dinosaur types and a mix of vibrant colors. Two figures are Theropods (like a Tyrannosaurus Rex), standing on two feet with short forearms: one is a vibrant medium green with black feet, and the other is a mottled green and yellow. A third figure, also a Theropod, is a solid bright yellow and is posed in a sitting position. All three Theropods have simple, stylized features with stitched smiles and black dot eyes. The fourth figure is a Triceratops, distinguished by its four-legged stance, bright orange body, a small white horn, and a prominent white felt frill around its head.
